OL,4,Clegalised in Jersey by 2027
OL,6,FIn a statement, the Minister for
OL,7,FHealth and Social Services, Deputy Tom
OL,8,FBinet, said: "The Government of Jersey
OL,9,Fcommenced work on assisted dying in
OL,10,F2020.
OL,12,F"Since then, we have seen a number of
OL,13,Fother jurisdictions bring forward
OL,14,Fassisted dying laws, however none of
OL,15,Fthose jurisdictions have undertaken
OL,16,Fsuch an extensive process of
OL,17,Fdevelopment or brought forward such
OL,18,Fcomprehensive draft legislation.
